Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.64,0:00:04.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Encounters are mysterious!\NBut the world is even more so!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.94,0:00:07.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm so glad I'm with you!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.06,0:00:09.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Today's all deduction!\NLet's change our view of people sometimes!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.32,0:00:11.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He sees the\Nsingle truth for what it is,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.86,0:00:13.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and looks like a kid\Nbut has the mind of an adult!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.90,0:00:16.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,His name? Detective Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.50,0:01:56.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks to Ran's plan to\Nbring her parents back together,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.55,0:01:59.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,we came to a midsummer beach.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.64,0:02:05.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But a girl we met fell into critical\Ncondition after a sea snake bit her.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.98,0:02:12.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This was no accident! It's a\Ncriminal act disguised as an accident!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.82,0:02:18.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"The Scuba Diving Murder Case (Part 2)."
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.86,0:02:23.33,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Queen Hotel, Izu
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.03,0:02:25.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What? Bring her insurance\Ncard to the hospital right away?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.16,0:02:29.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The hospital staff\Nsays it'd be best to have it,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.96,0:02:33.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,plus I feel all alone...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.17,0:02:37.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kiwako always takes it when traveling,\Nso it should be somewhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.09,0:02:41.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But never mind that! How is she?!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.89,0:02:45.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She's still in the Intensive Care Unit.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.85,0:02:47.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I think her condition's gotten worse.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.72,0:02:53.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The doctors keep rushing in and out,\Nbut they won't tell me anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.19,0:02:55.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you think she might die?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.61,0:02:58.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You idiot! What kind of crap is that?!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.40,0:03:01.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll get her insurance card and\Nbe right there! Just wait quietly!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.82,0:03:06.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You and Kiwako are\Nin the same room, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.24,0:03:08.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.21,0:03:13.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh no! The card key is still in the room!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.38,0:03:17.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I forgot it when she asked me\Nto get a bath towel from our room.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.75,0:03:18.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What do we do?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.21,0:03:21.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It locks automatically,\Nso we can't get inside.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.05,0:03:23.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sheesh.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.76,0:03:28.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll call the front desk from our\Nroom and have 'em bring a spare key.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.68,0:03:35.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, that's right. Room 406. Yes. Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.40,0:03:37.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks. Sorry for the bother.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.78,0:03:42.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.03,0:03:45.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,W-What is it, kid?\NDon't scare me like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.82,0:03:50.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You all went scuba\Ndiving around noon, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.33,0:03:52.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.08,0:03:55.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Did you catch anything?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.25,0:03:56.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Like fish.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.42,0:03:59.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, I didn't get anything this time.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.55,0:04:01.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What about the others?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.30,0:04:02.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I dunno.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.97,0:04:06.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We're familiar with these waters,\Nand we all did our own thing,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.76,0:04:09.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,so I'm not sure who did what.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.43,0:04:13.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I think Masahiko and Kiwako-{\i1}chan\N{\i0}wore matching wetsuits
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.89,0:04:16.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and did their diving\Nat the same spot, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.73,0:04:18.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They're really close!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.40,0:04:23.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. Them and Hiroshi\Nare all childhood friends.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.32,0:04:26.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They've always had fun\Ntogether, since they were kids.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.57,0:04:29.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They're all classmates?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.16,0:04:32.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, Hiroshi and Masahiko\Nare the same age as me,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.66,0:04:36.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but Kiwako-{\i1}chan {\i0}is one year younger,\Nthe same age as Harumi-{\i1}chan{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.21,0:04:44.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,To be honest, I planned to quit\Nthis club my second year of college.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.30,0:04:47.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But I changed my mind\Nwhen Kiwako-{\i1}chan{\i0}'s group joined.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.60,0:04:50.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I guess it was love at first sight.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.31,0:04:52.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.89,0:04:58.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How stupid!\NWhy am I telling all this to a kid?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.02,0:05:01.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait a minute!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.03,0:05:04.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Does that mean--?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.82,0:05:08.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That person and that person...\NCould it be?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.50,0:05:14.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There you are.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.45,0:05:15.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.83,0:05:16.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's see...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.34,0:05:24.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Insurance card, insurance card...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.80,0:05:29.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Geez! Here's where you left it!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.85,0:05:34.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I assume this is your card key?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.35,0:05:35.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.81,0:05:39.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Can you help me?\NI can't find Kiwako's insurance card.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.36,0:05:43.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Did she maybe forget it?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.86,0:05:47.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Inside the towel at the bottom of the bag.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.16,0:05:50.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just look.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.20,0:05:55.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The towel at the bottom of the bag...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.54,0:05:59.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,H-Here it is! How did you know?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.08,0:06:03.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My grandmother taught it to me\Nwhen I was a kid, and I taught them.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.21,0:06:08.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's childhood friends for ya!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.01,0:06:10.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not the only one.\NMasahiko knows it, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.47,0:06:17.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Say, Detective. You have a car, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.43,0:06:19.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. It's a rental.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.60,0:06:24.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then could you drive\Nus three to the hospital?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.36,0:06:25.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, no problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.86,0:06:29.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then let me come, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.24,0:06:32.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm worried about Kiwako-{\i1}san{\i0}...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.03,0:06:35.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't be stupid.\NFive people can't fit in that tiny car.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.99,0:06:37.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.75,0:06:41.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's all right.\NI can drop her off at the hospital.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.21,0:06:45.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What are those suitcases for, Mom?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.09,0:06:51.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, you can't tell? As soon\Nas I drop you off, I'm going home.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.97,0:06:53.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait, Mom!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.68,0:06:56.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't want to share the same\Nspace with this lunkhead anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.81,0:06:59.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Eri.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.43,0:07:00.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.77,0:07:02.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We need to talk later.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.60,0:07:06.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh? What about?\NI can't wait to find out.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.69,0:07:09.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come on!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.58,0:07:18.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're going too fast, Mom!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.83,0:07:24.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sheesh. You don't have to sulk\Nbecause he didn't notice your ring.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.58,0:07:27.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's not the ring. It's the incident.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.25,0:07:28.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The incident?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.80,0:07:34.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Not everything adds up yet,\Nbut this is clearly a murder case.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.85,0:07:35.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Murder?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.26,0:07:40.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And I'm angry at him\Nfor not even realizing it!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.64,0:07:46.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. It's a murder case,\Nand I have an idea who's responsible.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.90,0:07:49.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's just one\Nthing I don't understand...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.23,0:07:54.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why did that person do that then?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.07,0:07:56.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What could it be?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.95,0:07:58.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you mean the incident?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.20,0:08:01.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, what he wants to tell me.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.37,0:08:03.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He said we have to talk later.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.71,0:08:04.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.04,0:08:10.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Divorce... Custody rights... Or perhaps...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.59,0:08:13.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mom...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.97,0:08:19.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's probably nothing at all.\NHe's only testing me.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.35,0:08:22.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Testing?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.48,0:08:23.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's always the same.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.73,0:08:27.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He gets me worked up\Nand then watches me squirm.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.56,0:08:29.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's so self-conceited!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.69,0:08:33.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now I see! So that's what the deal is!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.49,0:08:38.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ran. Sorry, but I can't stand it anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.87,0:08:40.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mom!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.66,0:08:49.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No question about it!\NThat person is behind this!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.01,0:08:57.97,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,West Izu Hospital
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.97,0:08:57.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Masahiko! I brought it!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.97,0:08:59.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kiwako's insurance card!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.93,0:09:01.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Everyone!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.35,0:09:03.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So, how's her condition?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.48,0:09:05.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How is she, Brother?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.23,0:09:09.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know. She's still in the ICU.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.36,0:09:13.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let me know when you find out how she is.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.69,0:09:18.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're leaving, Mom?!\NBut Dad said he has to talk with you!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.07,0:09:24.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Talk? Do I really need to\Nlend my ear to that lady-killer?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.37,0:09:28.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, really?! You're fans of mine?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.08,0:09:29.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dad!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.83,0:09:34.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What a lost cause.\NMaybe I should give the guy a hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.01,0:09:36.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Say, Nurse.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.38,0:09:36.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.97,0:09:39.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I have a favor to ask.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.22,0:09:44.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait, Mom!\NHe can't help it! He's famous!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.89,0:09:50.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's all smiles at a time like this!\NI've had enough of his callousness!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.11,0:09:53.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But that's because--
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.07,0:10:03.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Paging Kisaki Eri and Matsuzaki\NHarumi from the Queen Hotel.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.74,0:10:06.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please come to the hospital\Ndirector's office immediately.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.16,0:10:09.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mori Kogoro is waiting.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.58,0:10:08.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Alright!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.42,0:10:11.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Me?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.51,0:10:20.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mori-{\i1}san{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.51,0:10:20.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you okay?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.05,0:10:22.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait! Little boy!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.39,0:10:25.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry! I'll bring it right back!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.48,0:10:32.19,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Director
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.85,0:10:32.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why did you call us here like that?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.61,0:10:35.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you have something\Nto tell me, just say it already!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.98,0:10:37.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mom...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.53,0:10:38.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yikes...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.90,0:10:42.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Umm, I can come\Nback later if I'm in the way.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.57,0:10:44.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm concerned about Kiwako, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.83,0:10:47.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So you are concerned about her?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.87,0:10:49.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Can't say I blame you.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.66,0:10:54.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,After all, the difference between murder\Nand attempted murder hangs in the balance.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.30,0:10:58.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. That wasn't an accident.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.38,0:11:02.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It was a premeditated act meant to kill.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.84,0:11:08.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Someone purposely had\Nthe sea snake bite Kiwako-{\i1}san{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.43,0:11:11.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Matsuzaki Harumi-{\i1}san{\i0}...\Nthat someone was you!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.36,0:11:14.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You can't be serious!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.44,0:11:15.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The fang marks.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.94,0:11:17.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Fang marks?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.48,0:11:20.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sea snakes have rather small heads.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.40,0:11:24.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If one bit a human, it'd be\Nsomewhere small, like a fingertip.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.24,0:11:28.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yet, Kiwako-{\i1}san{\i0}'s fang marks\Nwere on the back of her hand,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.91,0:11:31.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,where a sea snake couldn't have bitten her.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.83,0:11:38.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When rushing to help, she held the\Nhead of the snake she had hidden,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.00,0:11:42.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,forced its mouth open,\Nand had it bite down as if it had attacked.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.59,0:11:45.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't that right, Harumi-{\i1}san{\i0}?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.01,0:11:51.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see. You pretended to play\Ndumb but actually saw through it all.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.35,0:11:54.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then tell us this, Great Detective.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.23,0:11:57.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How can you be sure it was Harumi-{\i1}san{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.69,0:12:01.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Couldn't any of\Nthe others have done it too?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.24,0:12:05.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Besides, it was by sheer chance\Nthat Kiwako-{\i1}san {\i0}started to drown.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.20,0:12:10.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And what if it wasn't by chance?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.12,0:12:13.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What if Kiwako-{\i1}san\N{\i0}had done it on purpose?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.87,0:12:16.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,On purpose? What for?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.84,0:12:21.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's natural for lovers to want\Nto know the other's true feelings.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.26,0:12:26.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,To arouse the other's interest,\None might get close to another person,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.01,0:12:29.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,or even purposely\Nnot wear a wedding ring...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.72,0:12:32.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then, you're saying Kiwako-{\i1}san{\i0}...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.27,0:12:33.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.77,0:12:39.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kiwako-{\i1}san {\i0}pretended to drown\Nto test Masahiko-{\i1}san{\i0}, her fiancé.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.65,0:12:44.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,To see if he would come to her rescue,\Neven though he can't swim.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.36,0:12:52.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,As proof, she murmured this\Nafter confirming that he tried to help...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.33,0:12:54.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"That's a relief..."
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.21,0:13:00.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But they're getting married\Nnext week. Why do that now?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.46,0:13:03.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She wanted to be extra sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.76,0:13:07.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She was irritated that\Nher fiancé didn't even bat an eye
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.26,0:13:10.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,when she clung to this famous celebrity.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.93,0:13:16.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And then she executed the fake\Ndrowning plan they made in advance.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.02,0:13:18.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"They"?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.56,0:13:20.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. Two people.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.86,0:13:27.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,For the plan to work, someone had to\Ntell Masahiko-{\i1}san {\i0}right away.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.91,0:13:34.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It'd be a disgrace if someone\Nelse on the beach rescued her first.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.58,0:13:39.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And that other person was you, Harumi-{\i1}san{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.42,0:13:44.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The signal for the start of the\Nplan was probably when she said...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.51,0:13:47.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Could you get a fresh\Nbeach towel from our room?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.84,0:13:51.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Or so I'd assume. After that...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.05,0:13:53.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Later, Harumi! Don't forget!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.64,0:13:58.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...Is something else she said,\Nso that sounds about right.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.94,0:14:03.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But Harumi-{\i1}san {\i0}tried to\Nstop her from going into the water!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.07,0:14:08.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Besides, she wouldn't have\Ndone that in front of a famous detective!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.74,0:14:12.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's why she tried to stop her.\NBecause I was right there watching.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.83,0:14:16.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You don't have to do it today.\NCan't you go tomorrow?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.75,0:14:18.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll be fine!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.75,0:14:23.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But Kiwako-{\i1}san {\i0}continued\Nwith the plan anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.21,0:14:28.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Unaware that Harumi-{\i1}san\N{\i0}had another, more sinister plan in store.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.97,0:14:31.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Y-You can't be serious...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.18,0:14:34.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Upon returning to her\Nroom to get the bath towel,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.68,0:14:38.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Harumi-{\i1}san {\i0}concealed\Nher sea snake in her pouch
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.02,0:14:41.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and went back to the seaside restaurant.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.98,0:14:49.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then, at the proper time,\Nshe signaled Kiwako-{\i1}san {\i0}to falsely drown.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.11,0:14:51.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then, when rushing\Nto help with everyone else,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.70,0:14:57.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,she took out the hidden sea\Nsnake and had it bite Kiwako-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.62,0:15:01.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But what's your plan, Great Detective?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.71,0:15:06.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The murder weapon is gracefully\Nswimming in the Pacific Ocean.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.13,0:15:11.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Without a weapon,\Nthis case won't stand up in court.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.22,0:15:16.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I already told you. She placed\Nthe sea snake in her waist pouch.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.72,0:15:21.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's more, whether\Nout of confidence or confusion,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.44,0:15:24.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,she never left our side after the incident.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.44,0:15:29.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It should still be there in her pouch:
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.07,0:15:33.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,adhesive tape with black-banded\Nsea krait scales still attached!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.66,0:15:34.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tape?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.45,0:15:35.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.49,0:15:40.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Simply stuffing it in would make\Nit seem unnatural when taking it out,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.91,0:15:43.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and there'd be a chance\Nit could bite her fingers instead.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.92,0:15:50.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She most likely taped the snake\Ndown in several spots in the pouch
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.17,0:15:53.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and left only the\Nsnake's head sticking out.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.55,0:15:58.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That way, she could pull it\Nout and have it bite in an instant.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.77,0:16:03.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then the wing-like things\NI saw on the snake were...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.02,0:16:05.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Probably some of the tape.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.52,0:16:09.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The rest of the tape is\Nprobably still inside her pouch.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.11,0:16:12.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Inside her pouch?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.07,0:16:16.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But we still don't know\Nfor sure she put a snake in--
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.16,0:16:18.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We do. Because of her card key.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.24,0:16:22.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,As soon as I saw her compact,\Nwallet, and everything
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.96,0:16:27.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,on top of the card key\Nshe left in the room, it hit me
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.63,0:16:32.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,that she might've emptied her\Npouch and put something else in it.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.63,0:16:37.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But why would she harm Kiwako-{\i1}san{\i0}?!\NShe's her brother's fiancée!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.55,0:16:41.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is purely speculation,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.14,0:16:46.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but I wonder if Harumi-{\i1}san\N{\i0}might've liked Masahiko-{\i1}san{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.86,0:16:51.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No... loved him. A lot.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.19,0:16:56.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't be silly, Dad! She and\NMasahiko-{\i1}san {\i0}are brother and sister!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.41,0:16:59.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No. They probably aren't.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.95,0:17:06.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If they were, all four in their group\Nwould've been childhood friends.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.50,0:17:10.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Especially given that she's\Nthe same age as Kiwako-{\i1}san{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.21,0:17:15.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then they're step-siblings\Nfrom when their parents remarried?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.22,0:17:17.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. Probably.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.30,0:17:22.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Seeing as Hiroshi-{\i1}san {\i0}calls her\N"-{\i1}san{\i0}" even though she's younger,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.68,0:17:26.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,they were probably\Nin college when it happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.14,0:17:29.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No. It was my second year in high school
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.56,0:17:34.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,when my mom remarried\Nand I first met Masahiko-{\i1}san{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.11,0:17:40.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's a little helpless\Nbut nice, and I fell for him.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.45,0:17:44.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I never had anyone\Nlike him around me before.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.08,0:17:47.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But Kiwako-{\i1}san {\i0}was always by his side.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.25,0:17:54.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Whenever she spoke about\Nhis childhood, I'd get very sad and angry.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.59,0:17:59.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It was like she was saying,\N"You don't know anything about him!"
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.47,0:18:05.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My only choice was to hide\Nmy feelings and call him my brother.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.68,0:18:11.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Their sudden engagement\Nand marriage was a huge shock.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.81,0:18:17.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,To top it all off, she came to\Nme with that plan, knowing how I felt.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.07,0:18:19.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Almost as if she was mocking me.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.16,0:18:21.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Pretending to drown?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.57,0:18:24.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please? Can you do it?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.58,0:18:26.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And then you devised your own plan?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.91,0:18:28.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.62,0:18:33.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't want to hand\NMasahiko-{\i1}san {\i0}over to her! So I...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.96,0:18:34.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So I...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.42,0:18:42.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm so stupid, aren't I?\NDoing that would only make him sad...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.43,0:18:47.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm really so stupid...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.27,0:18:54.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're Toda Kiwako-{\i1}san{\i0}'s friends, correct?!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.65,0:19:00.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We managed to administer\Nan antitoxin just in time!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.24,0:19:03.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A few more days and she'll be just fine!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.87,0:19:06.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's all thanks to\Nyour emergency treatment!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.24,0:19:07.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It was nothing!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.58,0:19:09.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's wonderful news, Kiwako!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.75,0:19:11.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,W-Where's Harumi?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.58,0:19:13.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She's here! Harumi!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.09,0:19:25.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,C'mon! Why so bashful?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.81,0:19:27.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.52,0:19:35.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't know how you felt...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.06,0:19:41.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I had no idea, until I saw your\Nserious look when you rushed to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.91,0:19:44.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kiwako...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.07,0:19:51.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yet, I asked you for that favor...\NI'm really sorry! I regret it!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.50,0:19:58.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What are you saying?!\NI tried to... I tried to...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.67,0:20:02.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,W-Wait! Did something happen?!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.09,0:20:12.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's nothing. I was punished\Nfor testing the heart of another.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.19,0:20:15.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's why a sea snake bit me.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.23,0:20:19.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's all.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.82,0:21:53.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That was amazing\Ndetective work again, Dad!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.94,0:21:56.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sometimes I can't\Nremember anything at all...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.53,0:22:01.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Plus, it sounds like\Nyou noticed what Mom did.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.17,0:22:06.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh? Noticing but pretending\Nnot to know is all the worse.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.65,0:22:08.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mom!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:08.11,0:22:09.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's she talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.30,0:22:11.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Look at you playing dumb again!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.75,0:22:13.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She's talking about the ring!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:13.51,0:22:14.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ring?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.52,0:22:16.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, that's--!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:16.41,0:22:17.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:18.56,0:22:20.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You mean this?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.02,0:22:23.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No way!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:23.77,0:22:28.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I found it under the\Nbeach umbrella you were using.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:29.28,0:22:33.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How did you know I lost my ring there?!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:34.04,0:22:40.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't be stupid. Nobody dries\Ntheir hair with their glasses on.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:40.71,0:22:44.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That was evidence you\Nwere looking for something.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:44.55,0:22:50.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,People really only lose contacts,\Nearrings, and rings on beaches.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:51.26,0:22:55.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So the sand on your knees was\Nbecause you were looking for the ring!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:55.89,0:22:59.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I get it! You wanted\Nto tell her about the ring!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:59.31,0:23:02.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The old guy did notice!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:02.69,0:23:06.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Geez. If only he was always that sharp.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:07.03,0:23:09.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Besides, could you be any more obvious?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:09.90,0:23:14.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Drinking tea with your left hand,\Nwringing your hands nervously...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:14.28,0:23:16.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I couldn't help it...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:17.41,0:23:20.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mori Kogoro-{\i1}san{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.04,0:23:21.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hi!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:29.54,0:23:32.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dad! Hey, Dad!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.61,0:23:34.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mom! Mom!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:35.35,0:23:37.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mom!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.24,0:23:41.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Alright! Next time for sure!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:41.60,0:23:44.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It'll never, ever happen.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:02.13,0:24:03.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They match perfectly!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:03.79,0:24:09.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I wonder why the ones in chapters\None through six are all slightly off.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:09.80,0:24:12.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He obviously copied an earlier signature.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:12.96,0:24:14.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why would he do that?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:14.88,0:24:17.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Because he didn't want to write it anymore...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:18.66,0:24:20.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...or he couldn't anymore?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:20.51,0:24:25.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That means Shinmei-{\i1}sensei\N{\i0}might already be dead, doesn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:25.95,0:24:27.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,On the next Conan--
Dialogue: 0,0:24:27.37,0:24:30.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"The Mystery Writer\NDisappearance Case (Part 1)."
Dialogue: 0,0:24:47.21,0:24:49.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Next Conan's hint:
Dialogue: 0,0:24:49.59,0:24:51.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,One half.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:51.46,0:24:53.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Next episode is a mystery \Nabout a mystery writer.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:53.44,0:24:55.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The most mysterious thing \Nof all is the mystery.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:55.52,0:24:56.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:56.62,0:24:58.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,
